Gurston Butterman wasn’t listening. He was deep in thought. He was swimming in deep waters of cognition, freediving now, pressurizing dangerously... fearlessly... Thomas poked him in the shoulder. His eyes snapped open. “I’ve got it!” he exclaimed.
“Please don’t say, ‘pickled dunkle’o’saurus fries,’ again.”
“What we need is a good morning’s sleep!” said ~retsub-notrug satisfiedly and satisfactorily. Thomas was perfectly satisfied with this answer and gave no further thought to whether PDF stood for “Prudence’s Delicate Fingers” or “Paul Died Forlornly” or “Please Don’t Faint” or anything like that. In fact, they both put far from their minds that ill-fated print job and the mysterious attractive woman in the jpg and headed out the door and checked into the nearest hotel and went to sleep.

