In the squares of sunlight on the wall, the shadow of Thomas grabbed the arms of the shades of Bus and Belasco and dragged them down into the darkness below the light, even as the square which had held Thomas's center of mass fractured into an ephemeral spiderweb of, again, striking beauty, if anyone had been in a position to take notice.

